5|$|Quantitative easing {{was widely}} {{used as a}} {{response}} to the financial crises that began in 2007, especially by the United States and the United Kingdom, and, to a lesser extent, the Eurozone. <b>The</b> <b>Bank</b> <b>of</b> <b>Japan</b> was the first central bank to claim to have used such a policy.|$|E
