25|$|In {{order to}} {{regularize}} {{the issuance of}} convertible banknotes, a central bank, <b>the</b> <b>Bank</b> <b>of</b> <b>Japan,</b> was established in 1882. The bank would stabilize the currency by centralizing the issuance of convertible banknotes. The first central banknotes were issued by <b>the</b> <b>Bank</b> <b>of</b> <b>Japan</b> in 1885. They were called Daikokusatsu (大黒札), and were convertible in silver.|$|E
